OL,3,CGovernment to be told to scrap short
OL,4,Cprison sentences
OL,6,F"We think that too many people go
OL,7,Finside for a short period of time.
OL,8,FThey then come out unprepared for
OL,9,Freintegration into the community. That
OL,10,Fshort sentence, if anything, has put
OL,11,Fthem back.
OL,13,F"If they've got a job, they've lost
OL,14,Fit. If they've got a home, very often
OL,15,Fthey've lost that. Family
OL,16,Frelationships are damaged. So instead,
OL,17,Fwe think stronger community-centered
OL,18,Fsentences can be more effective."
OL,26,@nD@AOUzD@aO]
