OL,3,CGovernment to be told to scrap short
OL,4,Cprison sentences
OL,6,FInstead of imprisonment, a far greater
OL,7,Fproportion of criminals would be given
OL,8,Fcommunity service, be monitored via
OL,9,Ftagging, and attend new Intensive
OL,10,FSupervision Courts (ISCs).
OL,12,FITV News was given exclusive access to
OL,13,FTeesside ISC, where they have been
OL,14,Fpiloting the scheme.
OL,16,FWe watched as offenders attended
OL,17,Fhearings with a judge, probation and
OL,18,Fother services to ensure they were
OL,19,Fprogressing with their rehabilitation.
